FBIS4-52726 "dreas093_c_94015" FBIS-EAS-94-093 Daily Report 13 May 1994 North Korea Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song SK1305050194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0418 GMT 13 May 94 SK1305050194 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- Messages of greetings came to the great leader President Kim Il-song from foreign party leaders on his birthday. The messages came from Inaam Raad, chairman of the Nationalist Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon; Angel Castro Lavarello, president of the National Executive Committee of the Left Revolutionary Union of Peru; Milud Al Mahdabi, general secretary of the permanent Secretariat of the Organization of Socialists in the Mediterranean; and John Odlum, leader of the Progressive Labour Party of Saint Lucia. They extend warmest congratulations to President Kim Il-song and wish him good health and a long life. They also express firm solidarity with the Korean people in their struggle for the peace and peaceful reunification of the Korean peninsula.
